<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKERS START SLOWLY, LOSE TO SEATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shawn Kemp had 31 points and eight rebounds in 25 minutes and the Seattle 
SuperSonics shot 59.2% Wednesday night to send the Lakers to their first loss 
of the exhibition season, a 131-113 decision before 13,843 at the San Diego 
Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Van Exel made 12 of 18 attempts, including four of seven three-pointers, 
en route to a game-high 33 points for the Lakers. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought at the outset our players were timid," Coach Del Harris said after 
the Lakers committed 20 turnovers against the SuperSonics' trapping, pressing 
defense. 
</P>
<P>
 After starting with three consecutive exhibition victories for the first time 
since 1989 -- beating the lottery-bound Clippers and Sacramento in all three -- 
the Lakers dropped to 3-1. Their next game is Friday night against the Orlando 
Magic as part of the four-team GTE Everything Pages Shootout at the Forum. 
SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
