<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLIPPERS MAKE EFFORT BUT FALL TO NUGGETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matt Fish, a hustling free-agent center from North Carolina Wilmington, 
livened up the Clippers' 96-90 exhibition loss to the Denver Nuggets before an 
announced crowd of 5,049 Wednesday night at the Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Fish, at 6 feet 11 and 265 pounds, challenged Nugget center Dikembe Mutombo as 
the Clippers overcame a 21-point deficit with a 20-4 run in the first 10 
minutes of the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Fish had seven points and three rebounds and nearly outplayed starting center 
Elmore Spencer, who had had seven points and four rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clippers, who trailed, 86-69, going into the final quarter, tied it at 
90-90 on a three-pointer by rookie swingman Eric Piatkowski with 2:20 left. But 
the Nuggets pulled it out with six consecutive free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Dehere led the Clippers with 21 points. CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
