<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES; MARINA'S CROUCH DECIDES TO PLAY SOFTBALL AT STANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marcy Crouch, a three-sport standout from Marina High, orally committed to 
play softball at Stanford, Marina girls' volleyball Coach Jason Bilbruck said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 As a junior pitcher last season, Crouch, twice a Times All-Orange County 
selection, led the Vikings to the Southern Section Division I championship.She 
pitched a one-hitter and struck out 10 in the Vikings' 2-0 victory over 
Foothill in the title game. Crouch finished last season with a 22-2 record, 
0.24 earned-run average, and she hit .337. 
</P>
<P>
 Crouch is also a standout in soccer and volleyball. Last soccer season, she 
was the defensive co-player of the year in the Sunset League and she had two 
assists in Marina's 3-0 victory over Palos Verdes Peninsula in the Division I 
championship game. The Vikings finished 28-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In volleyball, Crouch helped Marina to a fast start and a county top-10 
ranking early this season. She was named to the all-tournament team of the 
Orange County Championships. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
