<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A proposal for an Orange County Section will be made today at the Southern 
Section Council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal would create a section made up entirely of Orange County 
schools.It would begin in the 1995-96 school year. 
</P>
<P>
 If the proposal passes, it will be introduced at the State Federated Council 
meeting on Oct. 28-29. The county has 72 public and private schools. Officials 
said the smaller private schools would remain with the Southern Section. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Shortstop Julie Adams of Cypress High has orally committed to play softball at 
UCLA, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 She has been an All-Empire League first-team selection three times in softball 
and basketball and twice in volleyball. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena's Jennie Foyle has orally committed to play softball at Stanford, 
Bob Foyle, her father, said. 
</P>
<P>
 Foyle, a shortstop, hit .405 last season and was a first-team All-Century 
League selection. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Huntress has been hired as the varsity softball coach by Katella High, 
girls' Athletic Director Linda Whitney said.  
</P>
<P>
 Huntress, who will be a walk-on coach, coached the junior varsity team at 
Canyon last spring. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress has hired Skip Loomis as its varsity boys' soccer coach. Loomis 
returns to the job after having coached the team from 1979-85. 
</P>
<P>
 Loomis replaces Fred Leininger, who stepped down to take a full-time teaching 
position at another school. 
</P>
