<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARIE DUVAL; ACTRESS PERFORMED IN L.A. MELODRAMA 'THE DRUNKARD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marie Duval, 98, a featured performer in "The Drunkard," the perennial 
melodrama-olio stage feature that was seen at the old Theater Mart in Los 
Angeles from 1933 to 1959.She was a former Ziegfeld Girl who also sang on radio 
with Al Jolson and appeared at the Palace Theatre in New York, vaudeville's 
premiere performance house. During the performance of "The Drunkard," audiences 
were encouraged to hiss the villain and cheer the hero, then Miss Duval and the 
other cast members performed in the miscellany of musical numbers that 
followed. In Sacramento on Oct. 14. 
