<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EL SEGUNDO; 5-K RUN SUNDAY WILL AID LEUKEMIA BATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Donna Kahl lost her husband, Roger, to leukemia more than two years ago, but 
her fight against the disease continues. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday, runners and walkers will compete in Roger's Run, the annual 5-K 
race she helped organize five years ago to battle the disease. Kahl still works 
at the run, which raises money and tests potential bone-marrow donors. 
</P>
<P>
 Money raised at the race will help fund the National Bone Marrow Donor 
Program, which keeps a computerized registry of possible donors. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the race, call (310) 322-9114, Ext. 443. JAMES 
