<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK SIX PAYS OFF RECORD $1,010,221.40 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified bettor at Santa Anita on Wednesday hit what is believed to be 
the largest Pick Six in U.S. history -- $1,010,221.40. 
</P>
<P>
 Buoyed by a two-day carryover of $328,219, there was $1,424,041 bet Wednesday, 
and only one favorite -- Damad in the sixth race -- won during the sequence. 
</P>
<P>
 Flying Rey, a 14-1 shot, opened the Pick Six with a wire-to-wire victory, at 
$31.40; then came victories by Shiny Slew ($8.40), Damad ($4.80), Alta Blue 
($13), Romarin ($10.40) and Cup O Moonshine ($22.40). 
</P>
<P>
 The previous record for a Pick Six payoff in Southern California was 
$976,229.60, when there was one perfect ticket on Feb. 28, 1986. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
