 COUNTYWIDE 
</P>
<P>
 Bash, Chuckles to Aid Charity 
</P>
<P>
 The Exchange Club Child Abuse Center of Orange County hopes to scare up some 
funds during two Halloween week events scheduled Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The first event, sponsored by the Orange County Young Republicans, is a 
costume ball called "The Monster Bash." It will take place at 7 p.m. Saturday 
at the Red Lion Inn/Orange County Airport, 3050 Bristol St., Costa Mesa. The 
bash will include music, dancing, hors d'ouevres, a costume contest, card and 
palm reading, and a prize drawing. Admission is $30 per person. For more 
information, call Barbara Brickner at (714) 961-1754. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday's event, co-sponsored by the Child Or Parent Emergency Services group, 
is an evening at The Improv comedy club, 4255 Campus Drive, Irvine. Admission 
is $35 per person. The event features a 6 p.m. reception, 6:30 p.m. dinner and 
an 8:30 p.m. comedy show. For more information, call (714) 722-1107 or (714) 
836-3601. 
</P>
