<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTBALL FEVER KICKS OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Playing the "big game" is mostly a fantasy for football fans. Only 
muscle-bound bruisers need apply. But the NFL is sponsoring a football 
challenge for the average fan -- men, women or children -- with the NFL 
Air-It-Out competition, making stops in 19 cities around the country, including 
two in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 There are team events (reservations required) and individual attractions (open 
free to anyone). The four-person teams compete in a four-on-four flag-football 
tournament, matched up against other teams according to size, skill and 
experience. The winners will head to the Air-It-Out Super Bowl at Universal 
Studios, Orlando, Fla., in March. 
</P>
<P>
 The attractions open to spectators include the Gatorade Field Goal Challenge, 
Quarter Challenge, Down and Out, Stadium Moon Bounce and others. 
</P>
<P>
 The first four-on-four is Saturday and Sunday, at the UC Irvine campus 
all-purpose field, 8 a.m.-4 p.m. The next Air-It-Out takes place in Encino, at 
Balboa Park, Nov. 5-6. To sign up a team, call (310) 829-5226. LAURIE K. 
SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
