<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ANTELOPE VALLEY; 
SHUTTLE ENDEAVOUR HEADS TO FLORIDA ATOP JUMBO JET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The space shuttle Endeavour headed home Wednesday atop a special jumbo jet 
after it was forced to land at Edwards Air Force Base last week because of bad 
weather in Florida. 
</P>
<P>
 The orbiter's next flight is expected in January. On the first leg of its 
flight, the Endeavour will be taken to Dyess Air Force Base near Abilene, Tex., 
after a refueling stop at Biggs Army Air Field in El Paso.  
</P>
<P>
 The Endeavour crew gathered geological and environmental data of the Earth's 
surface while in space by using the Space Radar Laboratory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
