<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 10 STABBED, 6 INJURED IN JAIL FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ten inmates were stabbed and at least six more received other injuries in a 
riot at the Pitchess jail Wednesday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fight broke out just before 9 p.m. in a dorm at the East Facility of the 
Peter J. Pitchess Honor Rancho and involved all 140 inmates housed in that 
dorm, said Sgt. Ron Spear of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15-minute fight was between African American and Latino inmates, Spear 
said. Deputies broke up the riot with "sting ball" grenades and rubber bullets. 
</P>
<P>
 "The inmates broke up some toilets and used the shards of ceramic as weapons," 
Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two inmates in critical condition with chest wounds were airlifted to Henry 
Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia, said Los Angeles County Fire 
Department spokeswoman Charlotte Kramer. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other inmates were taken to Holy Cross Hospital in Mission Hills, where 
their conditions were listed as critical and serious, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the latest of a series of 52 such mass brawls between African American 
and Latino inmates at the jail this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
