<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCNAMEE QUITS COSTA MESA JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lisa McNamee, The Times Orange County girls' basketball coach of the year in 
1991 and '93, has resigned her post at Costa Mesa High School. 
</P>
<P>
 She has accepted an offer to coach Irvine Valley College's first-year women's 
basketball program, pending approval of the district board of trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 McNamee, 32, who coached Costa Mesa to the Southern Section Division III-A 
championship and a berth in the State Division III title game in 1993, spent 
two seasons at Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 "The girls who played for me were great at Costa Mesa," McNamee said. "It was 
a timing thing, an opportunity to go to the collegiate level came up and I 
jumped at it." 
</P>
<P>
 McNamee coached at Estancia from 1985 to '91. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
