<TEXT>
<P>
 Modem Makers to Merge: U.S. Robotics Inc. and Megahertz Holding Corp., leading 
makers of personal computer modems, agreed to merge in a stock transaction 
valued at $213 million.The deal blends U.S. Robotics' strength in desktop 
modems with Megahertz's power as the No. 1 maker of credit card-sized modems 
for portable computers. Projected revenue next year is $650 million. Megahertz 
will become a subsidiary of Skokie, Ill.-based U.S. Robotics but will maintain 
its operation in Salt Lake City. 
