<TEXT>
<P>
 Chrysler Plans Joint Venture in Vietnam: The auto maker, seeking to expand 
into new markets, said it hopes to build Jeeps, trucks and other vehicles in 
the country.The deal, expected to be formalized in a few months, would make 
Chrysler Corp. the first U.S. car maker to establish assembly operations in 
Vietnam, a relatively poor country with unknown potential. Chrysler officials 
said the company will probably start out with exports from North America, 
followed by assembly of import kits and eventually a full-fledged manufacturing 
operation. Earlier this month, Ford Motor Co. announced plans to open showrooms 
and service facilities in Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City (formerly Saigon). 
</P>
