<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: WYNN'S REPORTS 20% RISE IN 3RD QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wynn's International Inc., an Orange supplier of sealing products, 
petrochemical specialties products, automotive air conditioners and builders 
hardware supplies, reported third-quarter profits of $3 million, or 53 cents a 
share, an increase of 20% from the 1993 third quarter profit of $2.5 million, 
or 45 cents a share.Sales declined to $72.2 million from $73.2 million. Profit 
for the first nine months of 1994 increased 34%, to $9.1 million, or $1.60 a 
share, from $6.8 million, or $1.22 a share, a year ago. Sales were up 5%, to 
$225.9 million from $215 million. 
</P>
