<TEXT>
<P>
 China to Declare Factories Bankrupt: The government said it will soon declare 
bankrupt an unspecified number of state-owned factories that have been soaking 
up state subsidies with no hope of reversing their losses. The State Council, 
or Cabinet, will identify the firms in an imminent decree that will also 
specify how their debts and workers will be managed, the China Daily newspaper 
reported. State Councilor Li Tieying, in charge of economic restructuring, said 
last week that reforming the state sector will be Beijing's key focus for 
reform in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
