<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank Urges Russian Tax Reform: The system needs reform to prevent the budget 
deficit -- blamed for the recent ruble crisis -- from widening still further, 
the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development said. The bank urged 
reforms in both Russia and other former Eastern bloc countries and chided 
European Union countries for hampering such reform by erecting trade 
barriers.Russia sharply reduced its budget deficit in 1993 and during the first 
half of 1994. The deficit has since begun climbing again, to 10% of national 
output, even though the government has chopped spending this year. Tax revenues 
have slumped. The government has been forced to borrow from the central bank to 
cover the shortfall, swelling the money supply and rekindling inflation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
