<P>
 Eldorado Bancorp: The parent company of Eldorado Bank in Tustin recorded a 
profit of $768,000, or 28 cents a share, for the third quarter, 32% higher than 
the $584,000, or 21 cents a share, reported for the third quarter last year. 
For the first nine months of 1994, profit totaled $1.8 million, or 65 cents a 
share, contrasted with a net loss of $1.4 million, or 51 cents a share, for the 
same period last year. Total assets as of Sept. 30 were $311.4 million, down 
from the year-earlier figure of $327.1 million. 
</P>
