<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LONG BEACH; SKATERS MAY BE BANNED FROM DOWNTOWN SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials may put the brakes on roller skaters and skateboarders who whiz 
through certain downtown landmarks. 
</P>
<P>
 The Long Beach Convention Center, Civic Center Plaza, Lincoln Park and The 
Promenade, a downtown walkway next to Pine Avenue, are among the sites where 
skating would be prohibited under an ordinance being prepared by city 
attorneys. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposed ban, expected to go before the City Council in about two weeks, 
would extend to bicycle riding at the park and Civic Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard I. Backus, city traffic engineer, said minor damage caused by skaters 
at the newly remodeled convention center and concern for pedestrian safety 
prompted the proposed ban. JOHN CANALIS 
