<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LA MIRADA; SCHOOL WINS NATIONAL AWARD FOR ITS PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN COX 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gardenhill Elementary School has received a prestigious Blue Ribbon award from 
the U.S. Department of Education. 
</P>
<P>
 The department presents the award yearly to schools that score high during 
reviews of their leadership, educational programs, community support and 
teaching environment. Gardenhill was one of four schools in Los Angeles County 
that received the award. A total 276 public and private schools nationwide 
received the award this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Gardenhill Principal Christine Reasin praised school programs that emphasize 
geography, international relations and democracies around the world.  
</P>
<P>
 Norwalk-La Mirada Unified officials went to Washington recently to accept the 
award and meet with President Clinton. JOHN COX 
</P>
