COMMUNITY NEWS: LONG BEACH; GAS CO. GIVES DONATION TO SAVE OUR SHIPYARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Southern California Gas Co. has contributed $40,000 to a nonprofit 
organization that has been working to keep the Naval Shipyard in Long Beach 
open. 
</P>
<P>
 The contribution is one of the largest donations made to Save Our Shipyard, 
which has collected $187,000 from 191 people and businesses since November, 
said chairman Bill Gurzi. Most of the money goes to a lobbying firm in 
Washington, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 A shutdown would mean the loss of 3,000 jobs and $350 million in wages and 
contracts for the area, according to a city study. 
</P>
